:{"content":"i deprecations.","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#1309","metadata":{"content":"deprecations.","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#131","metadata":{"content":"sigue en `0.1`.","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#1310","metadata":{"content":"deprecations.","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#1311","metadata":{"content":"eprecations.","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#1312","metadata":{"content":"precations.","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#1313","metadata":{"content":"recations.","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#1314","metadata":{"content":"ecations.","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#1315","metadata":{"content":"cations.","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#1316","metadata":{"content":"ations.","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#1317","metadata":{"content":"tions.","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#1318","metadata":{"content":"ions.","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#1319","metadata":{"content":"ons.","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#132","metadata":{"content":"sigue en `0.1`.","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#1320","metadata":{"content":"ns.","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#1321","metadata":{"content":"s.","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#1322","metadata":{"content":".","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#1323","metadata":{"content":"### Added\n- SPEC **§9 Conformance**: condiciones normativas (MUST/SHOULD/MAY) para implementaciones\n  alternativas — parser (subset §1.1 + casos de fallo duro), linter (reglas core +\n  perfil, `errors=0` como gate), compilador (byte-identidad: meta universal + orden de\n  `derive`, JSON 2 espacios, LF), exit codes §3.1, tolerancia (qué NO puede rechazar un\n  consumidor) y round-trip (las herramientas que reescriben un `GAME.md` preservan\n  tokens desconocidos). Las suites `test/parser.js`, `test/conformance.js` y\n  `test/cli-errors.js` quedan como referencia ejecutable.\n- SPEC §7: semántica explícita de los campos `x-` — ignorados por validación, **no**\n  pasan al artefacto compilado (salvo que un perfil los derive explícitamente), y deben\n  preservarse en round-trip.","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#1324","metadata":{"content":"ícitamente), y deben\n  preservarse en round-trip. Antes el spec no decía qué pasaba con ellos al compilar.\n- Modelo de la mitad permisiva (tolerancia/round-trip) inspirado en el Open Knowledge\n  Format (OKF) de GoogleCloudPlatform/knowledge-catalog; la mitad estricta (gate\n  determinista) sigue siendo la propuesta de valor propia del protocolo.\n\n## [1.1.0] — 2026-07-07\n\nRelease **aditivo** sobre `1.0.0` (bump minor según [SPEC §7.0](./SPEC.md)): décimo\nperfil `advance-wars` completo, pipeline de extracción de sprites GBA, ejemplo\n`monster-rpg`, mutation audit del linter y correcciones menores. La *versión del\nprotocolo* (`SPEC.md` header, `version` de los `GAME.md`) sigue en `0.1`\n(`manifest.json` → `migrations.supported: [\"0.1\"]`); no hay cambios breaking ni\ndeprecations.","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#1325","metadata":{"content":".1\"]`); no hay cambios breaking ni\ndeprecations.\n\n### Added — ejemplo monster-rpg + mutation audit (`cd645d5`)\n- `examples/monster-rpg.GAME.md` + `monster-rpg.generated.js` + `monster-rpg.html`:\n  ejemplo mínimo del perfil raíz con demo HTML.\n- `test/mutation-manual.js`: mutation audit manual del oráculo del linter — 15 mutantes\n  quirúrgicos sobre `examples/monster-rpg.GAME.md`, 15/15 atrapados. Añadido a `npm test`\n  (no corre en CI).","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#1326","metadata":{"content":"pados. Añadido a `npm test`\n  (no corre en CI).","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#1327","metadata":{"content":"ados. Añadido a `npm test`\n  (no corre en CI).","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#1328","metadata":{"content":"dos. Añadido a `npm test`\n  (no corre en CI).","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#1329","metadata":{"content":"os. Añadido a `npm test`\n  (no corre en CI).","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#133","metadata":{"content":"igue en `0.1`.","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#1330","metadata":{"content":"s. Añadido a `npm test`\n  (no corre en CI).","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#1331","metadata":{"content":". Añadido a `npm test`\n  (no corre en CI).","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#1332","metadata":{"content":"Añadido a `npm test`\n  (no corre en 