0/20.","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#18","metadata":{"content":"del protocolo sigue en `0.1`.","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#180","metadata":{"content":"ation audit 20/20.","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#181","metadata":{"content":"tion audit 20/20.","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#182","metadata":{"content":"ion audit 20/20.","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#183","metadata":{"content":"on audit 20/20.","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#184","metadata":{"content":"n audit 20/20.","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#185","metadata":{"content":"audit 20/20.","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#186","metadata":{"content":"audit 20/20.","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#187","metadata":{"content":"udit 20/20.","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#188","metadata":{"content":"dit 20/20.","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#189","metadata":{"content":"it 20/20.","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#19","metadata":{"content":"del protocolo sigue en `0.1`.","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#190","metadata":{"content":"t 20/20.","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#191","metadata":{"content":"20/20.","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#192","metadata":{"content":"20/20.","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#193","metadata":{"content":"0/20.","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#194","metadata":{"content":"/20.","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#195","metadata":{"content":"20.","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#196","metadata":{"content":"0.","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#197","metadata":{"content":".","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#198","metadata":{"content":"### Added — roguelike a lo grande: mecánicas por datos, un solo generador, mundo continuo\n- **Mecánicas nuevas 100% data-driven** en el perfil `roguelike` y su ejemplo:\n  **llaves y puertas cerradas** (`generator.lockChance`/`keyChance` + tiles `key`/\n  `lockedDoor`; cerraduras mutuas entre salas; la llave abre AMBOS lados de forma\n  permanente), **jefe custodiando el cofre** (`boss`: tile/hp/damage — bloquea la\n  victoria hasta caer), **progresión por experiencia** (`progression.killsPerAtk`/\n  `maxBonus`: el ataque sube con las bajas) y **permadeath declarativo**\n  (`progression.permadeath`).","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#199","metadata":{"content":"death declarativo**\n  (`progression.permadeath`). 3 reglas nuevas de perfil (`generator-chance`,\n  `boss-fields`, `progression-fields`) → 136 reglas.\n- **Solvencia por construcción**: toda sala conserva ≥1 salida SIN cerrar, y como el\n  cofre aparece donde exploras (generación perezosa), nunca queda tras una puerta\n  cerrada — las llaves abren atajos y zonas extra. Verificado como invariante por BFS\n  en `npm test`.\n- **Un solo generador, dos motores POR CONSTRUCCIÓN**: el visor 2D\n  (`examples/roguelike.html`) deja de duplicar la generación y pasa a **importar la\n  misma lógica pura** (`game3d-logic.mjs`) que usa game3d — renderer fino sobre\n  funciones testeadas.","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#2","metadata":{"content":"turo. La versión del protocolo sigue en `0.1`.","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#20","metadata":{"content":"el protocolo sigue en `0.1`.","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#200","metadata":{"content":"3d — renderer fino sobre\n  funciones testeadas. `build-standalone` aprende a inlinear imports relativos de\n  módulos ESM (+2 chequeos) y el standalone sigue autocontenido.\n- **game3d, mazmorra en mundo continuo**: las salas se añaden contiguas a la escena\n  al explorar (comparten muro fronterizo, sin celdas duplicadas) y **los pisos se\n  apilan físicamente en vertical** — la cámara viaja con el jugador. **Minimapa 3D**\n  del grafo explorado (cubos por sala, pisos apilados, conexiones cerradas en rojo,\n  escaleras en azul) renderizado en una segunda pasada.","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#201","metadata":{"content":"leras en azul) renderizado en una segunda pasada.","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#202","metadata":{"content":"eras en azul) renderizado en una segunda pasada.","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#203","metadata":{"content":"ras en azul) renderizado en una segunda pasada.","okf_concept":"CHANGELOG.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"Changelog"}},{"id":"CHANGELOG.md#204","metad