:"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — *Gameplay as Data*"}},{"id":"README.md#225","metadata":{"content":"md)):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — *Gameplay as Data*"}},{"id":"README.md#226","metadata":{"content":"d)):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — *Gameplay as Data*"}},{"id":"README.md#227","metadata":{"content":")):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — *Gameplay as Data*"}},{"id":"README.md#228","metadata":{"content":"):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — *Gameplay as Data*"}},{"id":"README.md#229","metadata":{"content":":","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — *Gameplay as Data*"}},{"id":"README.md#23","metadata":{"content":".\n\n---\n\n## Estructura del repo","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — *Gameplay as Data*"}},{"id":"README.md#230","metadata":{"content":"- [x] **Perfil `tower-defense`** — nuevo género (8 claves: TOWERS/DMG_CHART/ENEMIES/ARMORS/WAVES/MAPS/ECONOMY/BALANCE) con reglas, perfil y ejemplo. → `S1`.\n- [x] **Deprecation policy** — nivel `deprecated` en el linter + regla `version-migration` + `MIGRATION.md` + `manifest.json` expone `migrations`/`deprecatedRules`. → `S2`.\n- [x] **Performance + helpers** — helpers compartidos (`tools/profile-helpers.js`), P1/P2/P3 (lint <50ms/10K datos) y edge cases del parser. → `S3`.\n- [x] **Governance** — `CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md`, `CODEOWNERS`, plantillas de issue/PR. → `S4.1`.\n- [x] **buildGame contenido 9/9** — `test/buildGame-content.js` cubre los 9 perfiles (tower-defense + 8). → `S4.2`.\n- [x] **Docs finales** — README/SPEC/CONTRIBUTING alineados a `v1.0.0`.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — *Gameplay as Data*"}},{"id":"README.md#231","metadata":{"content":"— README/SPEC/CONTRIBUTING alineados a `v1.0.0`. → `S4.3`.\n- [x] **Tag `v1.0.0`** — `package.json` en `1.0.0` y `git tag v1.0.0`. → `S4.4`.\n- [x] **Tests verde** — `npm test` corre las suites (parser, multi-genre, conformance, all-examples, cli-errors, buildGame-content, render-png, build-standalone, lifecycle, perf-smoke).\n\n```bash\nnpm test                                   # las suites\nnode tools/game-manifest.js /tmp/m.json && diff -q /tmp/m.json manifest.json   # sin drift\nnode tools/game-schema.js && git diff --quiet schemas/                        # sin drift\ngit tag -l | grep v1.0.0                                                    # release tag\n```\n\n### Fase CORTO completada ✅\n\nLa base CORTO (sobre la que se apoya MEDIANO):","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — *Gameplay as Data*"}},{"id":"README.md#232","metadata":{"content":"La base CORTO (sobre la que se apoya MEDIANO):\n\n- [x] **CI 8/8** — `node test/all-examples.js` pasa los `(md, gen)` pares: lint 0 errores + export sin-drift.\n- [x] **SPEC ↔ código sync** — sin reglas core ficticias; perfiles de SPEC §6 == `manifest.json`.\n- [x] **`lintGame` directo (sin wrapper)** — emite `profile-known`, `version-migration`, `required-fields` sobre `profile` (y nivel `deprecated` para reglas con ciclo de vida).\n- [x] **Conformance por regla** — `node test/conformance.js` cubre ≥1 caso inválido por regla por perfil.\n- [x] **Hints 100%** — toda regla emitida en `--agent` lleva `hint` (o fallback genérico).\n- [x] **Exit codes** — contrato `0/1/2` documentado (SPEC §3.1) y verificado por `test/cli-errors.js`.\n\n## Licencia\n\n[MIT](./LICENSE).","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — *Gameplay as Data*"}},{"id":"README.md#24","metadata":{"content":"---\n\n## Estructura del repo","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — *Gameplay as Data*"}},{"id":"README.md#25","metadata":{"content":"---\n\n## Estructura del repo","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — *Gameplay as Data*"}},{"id":"README.md#26","metadata":{"content":"---\n\n## Estructura del repo","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — *Gameplay as Data*"}},{"id":"README.md#27","metadata":{"content":"--\n\n## Estructura del repo","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — *Gameplay as Data*"}},{"id":"README.md#28","metadata":{"content":"-\n\n## Estructura del repo","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — *Gameplay as Data*"}},{"id":"README.md#29","metadata":{"content":"## Estructura del repo","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — *Gameplay as Data*"}},{"id":"README.md#3","metadata":{"content":"136 reglas + cruces opcionales con el motor)\n```\n\n- **`GAME.md`** es la *fuente única de verdad*: front-matter YAML (tokens) + cuerpo Markdown (doc).\n- **`game-lint.js`** valida refs, rangos, dimensiones y simetrías; y puede **cruzar** los tokens con el\n  código del motor (p. ej. tiles sólidos ↔ el `Set` de colisión, o \"knobs\" de balance declarados pero\n  no referenciados).\n- **`game-export.js`** compila los tokens a `window.GAME` (con derivaciones: `WILD_LIST`, `EVOLUTIONS`,\n  precios, mapas expandidos…).\n- El **motor consume con fallback embebido**: si el generado falta, el juego degrada con gracia.\n\n### Qué se vuelve dato","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — *Gameplay as Data*"}},{"id":"README.md#30","metadata":{"content":"## Estructura del repo","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — *Gameplay as Data*"}},{"id":"README.md#31","metadata":{"content":"## Estructura del repo","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — *Gameplay as Data*"}},{"id":"README.md#32","metadata":{"content":"# Estructura del repo","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — *Gameplay as Data*"}},{"id":"README.md#33","metadata":{"content":"Estructura del repo","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — *Gameplay as Data*"}},{"id":"README.md#34","metadata":{"content":"Estructura del repo","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — *Gameplay as Data*"}},{"id":"README.md#35","metadata":{"content":"structura del repo","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — *Gameplay as Data*"}},{"id":"README.md#36","metadata":{"content":"tructura del repo","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — *Gameplay as Data*"}},{"id":"README.md#37","metadata":{"content":"ructura del repo","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — *Gameplay as Data*"}},{"id":"README.md#38","metadata":{"content":"uctura del repo","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — *Gameplay as Data*"}},{"id":"README.md#39","metadata":{"content":"ctura del repo","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — *Gameplay as Data*"}},{"id":"README.md#4","metadata":{"content":"ego degrada con gracia.\n\n### Qué se vuelve dato\n\nCriaturas, ataques (con efectos), tipos, evolución, ítems, encuentros por zona, economía, balance,\n**arte** (paletas, siluetas, tiles), **sonido** (sfx de eventos), **interiores** (DSL ASCII + navegación),\n**entidades** del mundo (NPCs, entrenadores, warps), estado inicial del jugador y **textos** de sistema.\n\n### Qué sigue en código (por diseño)\n\nEl **layout/colocación** del terreno y la **lógica/render** (fórmulas, máquinas de estado, cámara, UI).\nEl protocolo tokeniza *datos*, no *lógica*. Ver [§7 de la spec](./SPEC.md).\n\n---\n\n## Inicio rápido\n\nRequisitos: **Node.js** (sin dependencias, sin `npm install`).\n\n```bash\n# Validar el documento de ejemplo (0 errores / 0 warnings)\nnode tools/game-lint.js examples/GAME.md","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — *Gameplay as Data*"}},{"id":"README.md#40","metadata":{"content":"tura del repo","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — *Gameplay as Data*"}},{"id":"README.md#41","metadata":{"content":"ura del repo","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — *Gameplay as Data*"}},{"id":"README.md#42","metadata":{"content":"ra del repo","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — *Gameplay as Data*"}},{"id":"README.md#43","metadata":{"content":"a del repo","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — *Gameplay as Data*"}},{"id":"README.md#44","metadata":{"content":"del repo","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — *Gameplay as Data*"}},{"id":"README.md#45","metadata":{"content":"del repo","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — *Gameplay as Data*"}},{"id":"README.md#46","metadata":{"content":"el repo","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — *Gameplay as Data*"}},{"id":"README.md#47","metadata":{"content":"l repo","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — *Gameplay as Data*"}},{"id":"README.md#48","metadata":{"content":"repo","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — *Gameplay as Data*"}},{"id":"README.md#49","metadata":{"content":"repo","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — *Gameplay as Data*"}},{"id":"README.md#5","metadata":{"content":"rnings)\nnode tools/game-lint.js examples/GAME.md\n\n# Compilarlo al artefacto consumible por un motor\nnode tools/game-export.js examples/GAME.md examples/game-data.generated.js\n\n# (opcional) Activar los cruces con un motor concreto\nGAME_ENGINE=../mi-motor/engine.js node tools/game-lint.js examples/GAME.md\n```\n\nEl ejemplo [`examples/GAME.md`](./examples/GAME.md) es un juego demo completo de 10×8 tiles: campo con\nencuentros, una casa con interior, un entrenador, un NPC, ítems y un starter — todo en ~60 líneas.\n\n---\n\n## Estructura del repo","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — *Gameplay as Data*"}},{"id":"README.md#50","metadata":{"content":"epo","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — *Gameplay as Data*"}},{"id":"README.md#51","metadata":{"content":"po","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — *Gameplay as Data*"}},{"id":"README.md#52","metadata":{"content":"o","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — *Gameplay as Data*"}},{"id":"README.md#53","metadata":{"content":"| Ruta | Rol |\n|---|---|\n| [`SPEC.md`](./SPEC.md) | **La especificación del protocolo** (formato, tokens, artefacto, 136 reglas — core §4 + perfiles §6; hints de arreglo en [`tools/rule-hints.js`](./tools/rule-hints.js) —, frontera datos/código). |\n| [`tools/yaml-min.js`](./tools/yaml-min.js) | Parser del subconjunto YAML (isomorfo Node/navegador). |\n| [`tools/game-lint-core.js`](./tools/game-lint-core.js) | Reglas de validación puras (`lintGame`), isomorfas. |\n| [`tools/game-lint.js`](./tools/game-lint.js) | CLI del validador (cruces con el motor opcionales vía `GAME_ENGINE`). |\n| [`tools/game-build-core.js`](./tools/game-build-core.js) | Compilación genérica dirigida por `profile.derive`; isomorfa.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — *Gameplay as Data*"}},{"id":"README.md#54","metadata":{"content":"enérica dirigida por `profile.derive`; isomorfa. |\n| [`tools/game-export.js`](./tools/game-export.js) | CLI del compilador → `game-data.generated.js`. |\n| [`examples/GAME.md`](./examples/GAME.md) | Documento de ejemplo mínimo y autocontenido. |\n| [`.github/workflows/ci.yml`](./.github/workflows/ci.yml) | CI: lint + sin-drift del generado. |\n| [`CONTRIBUTING.md`](./CONTRIBUTING.md) | Cómo proponer cambios + política breaking/versionado. |\n| [`CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md`](./CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md) | Código de conducta del proyecto. |\n| [`CODEOWNERS`](./CODEOWNERS) | Owners automáticos por ruta (`/tools/*`, `/profiles/*`). |\n| [`.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/`](./.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE) | Plantillas de bug report y feature request.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — *Gameplay as Data*"}},{"id":"README.md#55","metadata":{"content":"TE) | Plantillas de bug report y feature request. |\n| [`.github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE.md`](./.github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE.md) | Plantilla de PR (changelog, testing, breaking). |\n\n---\n\n## Estado","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — *Gameplay as Data*"}},{"id":"README.md#56","metadata":{"content":"changelog, testing, breaking). |\n\n---\n\n## Estado\n\n**Release `v2.18.0`** — aditivo. **Página del protocolo** en GitHub Pages\n(https://mauricioperera.github.io/game-protocol/) con selector **ES/EN/PT**: explica el\nproblema, la idea (un archivo, dos lectores), el pipeline real y los 14 perfiles a\npúblico semi-técnico; el listado de demos existente se preserva en `demos.html`. Más\nuna **auditoría de datos** que corrige 4 inconsistencias documentales (conteo de\nperfiles en `demos.html`/`CONTRIBUTING.md`, perfiles faltantes en `llms.txt`, 23 hints\nfaltantes en `tools/rule-hints.js`) y agrega un test que gatea la cobertura de hints a\nfuturo. 191 casos de conformidad, mutation audit 20/20.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — *Gameplay as Data*"}},{"id":"README.md#57","metadata":{"content":"191 casos de conformidad, mutation audit 20/20.","okf_concept":"README.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — *Gameplay as Data*"}},{"id":"README.md#58","metadata":{"content":"191 cas