EC.md#152","metadata":{"content":"n (§6).","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#153","metadata":{"content":"(§6).","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#154","metadata":{"content":"(§6).","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#155","metadata":{"content":"§6).","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#156","metadata":{"content":"6).","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#157","metadata":{"content":").","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#158","metadata":{"content":".","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#159","metadata":{"content":"| Rule | Level | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `frontmatter-present` | error | `---` fences present and parseable |\n| `required-fields` | error | `version`, `name` exist — plus `profile` when no profile descriptor is resolved; a loaded profile supplies its own `required` list (see §2) |\n| `profile-known` | error | `profile` resolves to a loadable profile (emitted by `lintGame` when `opts.profileId` is passed but no profile loaded) |\n| `version-migration` | warn/error | `version` vs the spec version supported by the tooling (`profile.specVersion`, core default `0.1`): **warn** if the GAME.md is older (file `<` supported → consult `MIGRATION.md`); **error** if the GAME.md is newer than the tooling supports (file `>` supported → upgrade tooling) |\n| `deprecated` | deprecated | A token","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#16","metadata":{"content":"ser.js` is its executable companion.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#160","metadata":{"content":"e tooling) |\n| `deprecated` | deprecated | A token/rule/profile marked `deprecated: {since, removedIn}` emits a lifecycle finding with `since`/`removedIn` (not an error; the rule still applies until `removedIn`) |\n| `section-order` | error/warn | `##` sections match the order declared by the profile |\n| `broken-ref` | error | Every cross-reference resolves to a declared token |\n| `dims` | error | Matrix/grid tokens match their declared dimensions |\n| `range` | error | Numeric tokens fall within declared bounds |\n| `dead-token` | warn | Tokens not referenced by engine code (optional, via `GAME_ENGINE`) |\n| `text-valid` | error | Declared text entries are non-empty strings |\n| `no-drift` | error (CI) | Generated artifact matches current `GAME.md` |","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#161","metadata":{"content":"| Generated artifact matches current `GAME.md` |\n\n> `broken-ref`, `dims`, `range` (and `enum`) are **rule families**: the profile supplies *which* tokens they apply to and *what* the bounds/dimensions/values are. The core supplies the checking machinery. All four are **declarative tables** in the profile descriptor (§6.1): `refs` (broken-ref; `msg` optional — the core generates a default message), `bounds` (range: `gt`/`min`/`max`/`integer`/`required` over collection or singleton fields), `dims` (fixed-shape matrices) and `enums` (closed value sets). Non-uniform logic stays in `rules` functions — a profile that needs none of them can ship as pure data (§6.1, §11).","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#162","metadata":{"content":"one of them can ship as pure data (§6.1, §11).\n\n> `profile-known` and `version-migration` are emitted by `lintGame` itself (not only by the CLI wrapper), so a direct consumer of the core (browser, other tool) that calls `lintGame(data, body, {profile, profileId})` receives them. The CLI wrapper still owns `profile-load-error` (a syntax error in a profile module), which requires filesystem access and does not belong in the isomorphic core.\n\n## 5. Cross-validation with the engine (optional)\n\nWhen `GAME_ENGINE` points at engine source, the linter can check synchronization between declared data and code (e.g. a token marked one way that the engine treats another, or balance keys the engine never reads). This is the core's `dead-token` family; profiles may extend it.\n\n## 6. Domain profiles","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#163","metadata":{"content":"; profiles may extend it.\n\n## 6. Domain profiles\n\nA **profile** is a declarative description of a genre's vocabulary. It specifies:\n\n1. **Token schema** — the tokens this genre adds (types, shapes, required/optional).\n2. **Section order** — the canonical `##` sequence for the Markdown body.\n3. **Reference graph** — which tokens reference which (drives the `broken-ref` family).\n4. **Bounds & dimensions** — feeds the `range` and `dims` families.\n5. **Derived keys** — how `export` turns tokens into the runtime object.\n6. **Profile-specific rules** — checks that only make sense in this genre.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#164","metadata":{"content":"* — checks that only make sense in this genre.\n\nThe core ships with **9 reference profiles** under `profiles/` (each a loadable `.js` module; `monster-rpg` and `tower-defense` also carry a human-readable `.md` companion). They exist to prove the core is genre-agnostic — every genre is expressed as a profile, never as a core change:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#165","metadata":{"content":"expressed as a profile, never as a core change:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#166","metadata":{"content":"expressed as a profile, never as a core change:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#167","metadata":{"content":"xpressed as a profile, never as a core change:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#168","metadata":{"content":"pressed as a profile, never as a core change:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#169","metadata":{"content":"ressed as a profile, never as a core change:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#17","metadata":{"content":"er.js` is its executable companion.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#170","metadata":{"content":"essed as a profile, never as a core change:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#171","metadata":{"content":"ssed as a profile, never as a core change:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#172","metadata":{"content":"sed as a profile, never as a core change:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#173","metadata":{"content":"ed as a profile, never as a core change:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#174","metadata":{"content":"d as a profile, never as a core change:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#175","metadata":{"content":"as a profile, never as a core change:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#176","metadata":{"content":"as a profile, never as a core change:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#177","metadata":{"content":"s a profile, never as a core change:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#178","metadata":{"content":"a profile, never as a core change:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#179","metadata":{"content":"a profile, never as a core change:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#18","metadata":{"content":"r.js` is its executable companion.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#180","metadata":{"content":"profile, never as a core change:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#181","metadata":{"content":"profile, never as a core change:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#182","metadata":{"content":"rofile, never as a core change:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#183","metadata":{"content":"ofile, never as a core change:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#184","metadata":{"content":"file, never as a core change:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#185","metadata":{"content":"ile, never as a core change:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#186","metadata":{"content":"le, never as a core change:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#187","metadata":{"content":"e, never as a core change:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#188","metadata":{"content":", never as a core change:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#189","metadata":{"content":"never as a core change:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#19","metadata":{"content":".js` is its executable companion.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#190","metadata":{"content":"never as a core change:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#191","metadata":{"content":"ever as a core change:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#192","metadata":{"content":"ver as a core change:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#193","metadata":{"content":"er as a core change:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#194","metadata":{"content":"r as a core change:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#195","metadata":{"content":"as a core change:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#196","metadata":{"content":"as a core change:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#197","metadata":{"content":"s a core change:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#198","metadata":{"content":"a core change:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#199","metadata":{"content":"a core change:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#2","metadata":{"content":"tter + Markdown body, separated by `---` fences.\n\n```\n---\n# tokens: the machine-readable contract\nversion: 0.1\nname: \"My Game\"\n...\n---\n\n# Overview\n...human-canonical documentation...\n```\n\n- **Front-matter (tokens):** the authoritative data. Edited here, *never* in generated output.\n- **Body (Markdown):** canonical prose. Section order is enforced by the active profile, not by the core.\n\n### 1.1 Supported YAML subset\n\nThe reference parser (`yaml-min.js`) supports, by design:\n\n- block maps (2-space indent, arbitrary nesting)\n- flow maps and flow lists (single line)\n- scalars: number, boolean, string (quoted/unquoted)\n- line comments (`# …`)\n\nNot supported: block sequences (`- item`), anchors/aliases, multiline strings. In flow context, commas inside text must be quoted.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#20","metadata":{"content":"js` is its executable companion.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#200","metadata":{"content":"core change:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#201","metadata":{"content":"core change:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#202","metadata":{"content":"ore change:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#203","metadata":{"content":"re change:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#204","metadata":{"content":"e change:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#205","metadata":{"content":"change:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#206","metadata":{"content":"change:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#207","metadata":{"content":"hange:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#208","metadata":{"content":"ange:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#209","metadata":{"content":"nge:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#21","metadata":{"content":"s` is its executable companion.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#210","metadata":{"content":"ge:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#211","metadata":{"content":"e:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#212","metadata":{"content":":","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#213","metadata":{"content":"| Profile | Genre | Key derived keys (subset) |\n|---|---|---|\n| `profiles/monster-rpg.js` (`monster-rpg.md`) | creature-collector RPG | `SPECIES`, `TYPE_CHART`, `MOVES`, `EVOLUTIONS`, `ENCOUNTERS`, `MAPS`, `ECONOMY` |\n| `profiles/adventure.js` | tile-based adventure / escape room | `SCENE`, `ENTITIES`, `PLAYER`, `TEXT`, `WIN` |\n| `profiles/dungeon.js` | dungeon crawler | `SCENES`, `ANIMATE`, `PLAYER`, `TEXT`, `WIN` |\n| `profiles/platformer.js` | 2D platformer | `TILESETS`, `ENEMIES`, `LEVELS`, `PHYSICS`, `SFX` |\n| `profiles/crafting.js` | crafting / recipe tree | `MATERIALS`, `ITEMS`, `STATIONS`, `RECIPES` |\n| `profiles/papers-please.js` | border-control / document inspection | `COUNTRIES`, `DOCUMENTS`, `RULES`, `ENTRANTS`, `DAYS` |\n| `profiles/roguelike.js` | procedural roguelike | `GENE","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#214","metadata":{"content":"files/roguelike.js` | procedural roguelike | `GENERATOR`, `ENEMY_POOL`, `ITEM_POOL`, `PLAYER`, `WIN` |\n| `profiles/voxel.js` | voxel / 3D structures | `MATERIALS`, `PREFABS`, `STRUCTURES`, `VOXELS` |\n| `profiles/tower-defense.js` (`tower-defense.md`) | tower defense | `TOWERS`, `DMG_CHART`, `ENEMIES`, `ARMORS`, `WAVES`, `MAPS`, `ECONOMY`, `BALANCE` |\n\n`monster-rpg` is the *first* application profile (the protocol grew out of a real mini-Pokémon engine), not the protocol itself. `tower-defense` was the second genre added, deliberately orthogonal to the first, to demonstrate that the core is genre-agnostic; the remaining seven broaden the coverage to platformer, crafting, document-inspection, roguelike and voxel genres.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#215","metadata":{"content":"document-inspection, roguelike and voxel genres.\n\n> **Tenth profile.** `profiles/advance-wars.js` serves the GBA sprite-extraction pipeline (`tools/SPRITE_EXTRACTION.md`): its vocabulary is `palettes` (16 BGR555-quantized colors, `[r,g,b]` in `0..31`) and `units` (4bpp tiles: a `height`×`width` matrix of nibbles `0..15` indexing the palette). Rules: `palette-color-range`, `unit-palette-ref`, `unit-dims`, `unit-tiledata-range`. Derived keys: `PALETTES`, `UNITS`. Its one reference (`units.*.palette` → numeric `palettes` keys) is validated in `rules`, not `refs` — same reason as `armors` in tower-defense (the broken-ref family matches string keys).","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#216","metadata":{"content":"nse (the broken-ref family matches string keys).\n\n> **Eleventh profile (pure-data).** `profiles/quiz.json` is the **data-only reference profile** (§6.1): no functions — loaded with `JSON.parse`, never executed (§10) — validating entirely through the declarative families (`refs` with default messages, `bounds`, `enums`). It exists to prove a genre can be a pure-data contract.\n\n> Further application profiles follow the same two patterns (`.js` with code under review, or data-only `.json`); **`manifest.json` is the canonical list** — this section documents the nine reference profiles plus the pattern, not an exhaustive inventory.\n\n> **Design intent.** If you can express a new genre as a profile without touching the core, the core is doing its job. If you cannot, that is a core bug.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#217","metadata":{"content":"oing its job. If you cannot, that is a core bug.\n\n### 6.1 Profile descriptor contract (normative)\n\nA profile module exports one object. Its shape is validated on load (`validateProfile` in `tools/profile-helpers.js`); a malformed descriptor is reported as `profile-load-error` with the offending entry, never as a runtime `TypeError` mid-lint.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#218","metadata":{"content":"entry, never as a runtime `TypeError` mid-lint.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#219","metadata":{"content":"entry, never as a runtime `TypeError` mid-lint.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#22","metadata":{"content":"` is its executable companion.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#220","metadata":{"content":"ntry, never as a runtime `TypeError` mid-lint.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#221","metadata":{"content":"try, never as a runtime `TypeError` mid-lint.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#222","metadata":{"content":"ry, never as a runtime `TypeError` mid-lint.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#223","metadata":{"content":"y, never as a runtime `TypeError` mid-lint.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#224","metadata":{"content":", never as a runtime `TypeError` mid-lint.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#225","metadata":{"content":"never as a runtime `TypeError` mid-lint.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#226","metadata":{"content":"never as a runtime `TypeError` mid-lint.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#227","metadata":{"content":"ever as a runtime `TypeError` mid-lint.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#228","metadata":{"content":"ver as a runtime `TypeError` mid-lint.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#229","metadata":{"content":"er as a runtime `TypeError` mid-lint.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#23","metadata":{"content":"is its executable companion.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#230","metadata":{"content":"r as a runtime `TypeError` mid-lint.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#231","metadata":{"content":"as a runtime `TypeError` mid-lint.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#232","metadata":{"content":"as a runtime `TypeError` mid-lint.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#233","metadata":{"content":"s a runtime `TypeError` mid-lint.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#234","metadata":{"content":"a runtime `TypeError` mid-lint.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#235","metadata":{"content":"a runtime `TypeError` mid-lint.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#236","metadata":{"content":"runtime `TypeError` mid-lint.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#237","metadata":{"content":"runtime `TypeError` mid-lint.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#238","metadata":{"content":"untime `TypeError` mid-lint.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md