"id":"SPEC.md#289","metadata":{"content":"collection aggregate (e.g.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#29","metadata":{"content":"s executable companion.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#290","metadata":{"content":"ollection aggregate (e.g.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#291","metadata":{"content":"llection aggregate (e.g.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#292","metadata":{"content":"lection aggregate (e.g.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#293","metadata":{"content":"ection aggregate (e.g.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#294","metadata":{"content":"ction aggregate (e.g.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#295","metadata":{"content":"tion aggregate (e.g.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#296","metadata":{"content":"ion aggregate (e.g.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#297","metadata":{"content":"on aggregate (e.g.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#298","metadata":{"content":"n aggregate (e.g.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#299","metadata":{"content":"aggregate (e.g.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#3","metadata":{"content":"flow context, commas inside text must be quoted.\n\n> **Known limitation.** This is a strict subset, not standard YAML. Implementations MAY swap in a full YAML parser; conformance only requires that the documented subset parses identically (see the grammar in §1.2).\n\n### 1.2 Formal grammar (normative)\n\nThe subset, as an EBNF-style grammar. This — not the reference parser's source — is the normative definition; `test/parser.js` is its executable companion.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#30","metadata":{"content":"executable companion.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#300","metadata":{"content":"aggregate (e.g.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#301","metadata":{"content":"ggregate (e.g.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#302","metadata":{"content":"gregate (e.g.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#303","metadata":{"content":"regate (e.g.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#304","metadata":{"content":"egate (e.g.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#305","metadata":{"content":"gate (e.g.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#306","metadata":{"content":"ate (e.g.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#307","metadata":{"content":"te (e.g.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#308","metadata":{"content":"e (e.g.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#309","metadata":{"content":"(e.g.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#31","metadata":{"content":"executable companion.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#310","metadata":{"content":"(e.g.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#311","metadata":{"content":"e.g.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#312","metadata":{"content":".g.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#313","metadata":{"content":"g.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#314","metadata":{"content":".","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#315","metadata":{"content":"dungeon: `warp.locked` must equal an `item` that *some* `pickups` entry, in *any* scene, grants) is expressed as data instead of a hand-written `rules` function |\n| `bounds` | entry[] | no | each: `{ rule, level?, collection\\|singleton, field, gt?, min?, max?, integer?, required?, msg?() }` — range family |\n| `dims` | entry[] | no | each: `{ rule, level?, collection, shape: [h, w] }` — dims family |\n| `enums` | entry[] | no | each: `{ rule, level?, collection\\|singleton, field, values: [..], required? }` — closed value sets |\n| `grids` | entry[] | no | each: `{ rule, emptyRule?, level?, collection\\|singleton, rowsField?, legendField?, fillField?, shape?: { singleton, rowsField?, colsField? }, legend?: { rule, level?, tileField?, tileTarget: { collection, allow? }, palField?, palMax?","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#316","metadata":{"content":"Target: { collection, allow? }, palField?, palMax? } }` — grid/legend family (§11): without `shape`, validates uniform row width (`rule`) and empty rows (`emptyRule`, defaults to `rule`) self-consistently (against the grid's own first row); with `shape`, validates row/col count against another singleton's fields instead (e.g. `platform.rows`/`.cols` for `monster-rpg`/`tower-defense` maps) and does not treat empty rows as an error on its own.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#317","metadata":{"content":"does not treat empty rows as an error on its own. Either way, each legend/fill symbol's `tile` (and optional `pal`) is checked against a target collection |\n| `rules` | function[] | no | non-uniform logic; each `fn(ctx)`, may carry `fn.deprecated = { since, removedIn }` (§7.1) |\n| `derive` | entry[] | no | each: `{ key, from \\| value \\| fn(data, helpers) }` — compilation table, in output order |\n\n**Trust note:** `refs`/`bounds`/`dims`/`enums`/`derive` are data, but `rules` and `derive.fn` are **executable code** — see §10.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#318","metadata":{"content":"derive.fn` are **executable code** — see §10.\n\n**Pure-data profiles.** A descriptor with no functions at all (`rules: []`, no `derive.fn`, no `refs[].msg`) MAY be shipped as **`profiles/<id>.json`**: the CLIs load it with `JSON.parse` — **no code is ever executed** — making it safe to consume from untrusted sources (§10). `profiles/quiz.json` is the reference pure-data profile; `manifest.json` marks such profiles with `dataOnly: true`. Resolution order: `<id>.js` first, then `<id>.json`.\n\n`test/profile-descriptor.js` is the executable reference: every shipped profile MUST validate, and each malformed shape MUST produce an actionable message.\n\n## 7. Versioning & extensibility","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#319","metadata":{"content":"nable message.\n\n## 7. Versioning & extensibility","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#32","metadata":{"content":"xecutable companion.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#320","metadata":{"content":"able message.\n\n## 7. Versioning & extensibility","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#321","metadata":{"content":"ble message.\n\n## 7. Versioning & extensibility","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#322","metadata":{"content":"le message.\n\n## 7. Versioning & extensibility","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#323","metadata":{"content":"e message.\n\n## 7. Versioning & extensibility","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#324","metadata":{"content":"message.\n\n## 7. Versioning & extensibility","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#325","metadata":{"content":"message.\n\n## 7. Versioning & extensibility","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#326","metadata":{"content":"essage.\n\n## 7. Versioning & extensibility","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#327","metadata":{"content":"ssage.\n\n## 7. Versioning & extensibility","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":