,{"id":"SPEC.md#349","metadata":{"content":"ng & extensibility","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#35","metadata":{"content":"utable companion.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#350","metadata":{"content":"g & extensibility","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#351","metadata":{"content":"& extensibility","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#352","metadata":{"content":"& extensibility","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#353","metadata":{"content":"extensibility","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#354","metadata":{"content":"extensibility","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#355","metadata":{"content":"xtensibility","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#356","metadata":{"content":"tensibility","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#357","metadata":{"content":"ensibility","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#358","metadata":{"content":"nsibility","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#359","metadata":{"content":"sibility","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#36","metadata":{"content":"table companion.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#360","metadata":{"content":"ibility","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#361","metadata":{"content":"bility","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#362","metadata":{"content":"ility","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#363","metadata":{"content":"lity","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#364","metadata":{"content":"ity","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#365","metadata":{"content":"ty","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#366","metadata":{"content":"y","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#367","metadata":{"content":"- **Spec version** uses semver. During `0.x` (pre-`1.0`): **breaking changes bump the minor** (`0.1` → `0.2`), **fixes and additive changes are a patch** (`0.1.0` → `0.1.1`). At `1.0` the core tokens are **frozen**: every removal of a core token or rule is a major bump and must go through the deprecation policy (§7.1) first.\n- **Profiles version independently** of the core; a `GAME.md` declares both (`version` for core, profile carries its own `specVersion`).\n- **The linter migrates, not rejects.** The core rule `version-migration` compares `data.version` against `profile.specVersion` (core default `0.1`): a GAME.md written for an older version is a **warning** pointing at `MIGRATION.md`, not an error — old files keep linting clean while the author migrates.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#368","metadata":{"content":"les keep linting clean while the author migrates. A GAME.md using a version newer than the tooling is an **error** (upgrade the tooling).\n- **Extension fields** use an `x-` prefix and are ignored by validation, allowing experiments without forking the spec. They are **not** copied into the compiled artifact — compilation emits only the universal meta plus the profile's `derive` keys — but a profile MAY expose one explicitly (a `derive` entry can read any token, `x-` included). Tools that rewrite a `GAME.md` (migrators, formatters, agent editors) MUST preserve `x-` and other unknown tokens (see §9, round-trip).\n\n### 7.0 Semver by example\n\nThe two versioning regimes, concretely:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#369","metadata":{"content":"example\n\nThe two versioning regimes, concretely:\n\n| Change | `0.x` (pre-`1.0`) | `1.0`+ (frozen core) |\n|---|---|---|\n| New token / section / rule (additive) | **patch** `0.1.0 → 0.1.1` | **minor** `1.0.0 → 1.1.0` |\n| Fix / clarification (no shape change) | **patch** `0.1.0 → 0.1.1` | **patch** `1.0.0 → 1.0.1` |\n| Rename / reshape a token or rule (breaking) | **minor** `0.1 → 0.2` (+ deprecation recommended) | **major** `1.0 → 2.0` (deprecation **mandatory** in `1.x` first) |\n| Remove a core token / rule | **minor** `0.1 → 0.2` (deprecation recommended) | **major** `1.0 → 2.0` (deprecation **mandatory** in `1.x` first) |\n\nWorked examples:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#37","metadata":{"content":"able companion.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#370","metadata":{"content":"*mandatory** in `1.x` first) |\n\nWorked examples:\n\n- **Add `BALANCE` to a profile (additive).** `0.x`: `0.1.0 → 0.1.1`; `1.0`+: `1.0.0 → 1.1.0`. Old `GAME.md` files keep linting clean (the new token is optional with a fallback).\n- **Rename `MOVES` → `ACTIONS` (breaking).** `0.x`: bump to `0.2`, mark `MOVES` `deprecated: {since: 0.2, removedIn: 0.3}`, add `MIGRATION.md` recipe; `1.0`+: mark deprecated in `1.1` (`removedIn: 2.0`), actually remove in `2.0`.\n- **Tighten a `range` bound from `1..99` to `1..50` (breaking, narrows valid inputs).** Treated as a reshape: same path as the rename row above. Files that used values in `51..99` must migrate.\n- **Fix `version-migration` false positive (fix, no shape change).** `patch` in both regimes.\n\n### 7.1 Deprecation policy","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#371","metadata":{"content":"ch` in both regimes.\n\n### 7.1 Deprecation policy\n\nThe protocol has a lifecycle: tokens, rules, and profiles can be **deprecated** (slated for removal) before they are **removed**. Deprecation is a contract between maintainers and authors — it says \"this still works today, but migrate; it disappears in `removedIn`.\"\n\n- **How to deprecate.** A profile rule is marked by attaching `rule.deprecated = { since, removedIn }` to the rule function. The linter emits a finding at the `deprecated` level:\n\n  ```js\n  function ruleOldX(ctx) { /* still validates... */ }\n  ruleOldX.deprecated = { since: '0.1', removedIn: '1.0' };\n  ```\n\n  ```json\n  { \"level\": \"deprecated\", \"rule\": \"ruleOldX\",\n    \"since\": \"0.1\", \"removedIn\": \"1.0\",\n    \"msg\": \"regla deprecada: se remueve en 1.0 (desde 0.1)\" }\n  ```","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#372","metadata":{"content":"eprecada: se remueve en 1.0 (desde 0.1)\" }\n  ```\n\n- **The `deprecated` level is not an error.** It does not break the gate: a deprecated file still lints with `errors: 0`. This is the one-major grace period. The rule keeps applying (it still validates data) until `removedIn`; only the finding signals the lifecycle.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#373","metadata":{"content":"ovedIn`; only the finding signals the lifecycle.\n\n- **Semver contract for removal.**\n  - A token/rule/profile deprecated at `since: S` is **supported through every release from `S` up to (but not including) `removedIn`**.\n  - Example: a rule deprecated `since: 0.2`, `removedIn: 1.0` is supported in `0.2`–`0.9.x` and **becomes a hard error / is removed in `1.0`**.\n  - During `0.x`, the actual removal is a **minor bump** (breaking, allowed pre-`1.0`). At `1.0`+, removal is a **major bump** and deprecation is **mandatory** the major before.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#374","metadata":{"content":"d deprecation is **mandatory** the major before.\n\n- **`manifest.json` exposes the lifecycle.** Each profile lists its `deprecatedRules: [{rule, since, removedIn}]`, and the top-level `migrations: { supported: [...], doc: 'MIGRATION.md' }` field declares which spec versions the current tooling supports and where the migration recipe lives.\n\n- **Changelog: deprecation vs. breaking.**\n  - A deprecation is logged under `### Deprecated` in `CHANGELOG.md` (`[Unreleased]`): \"Rule `X` deprecated (`since`, `removedIn`); use `Y` instead.\"\n  - The actual removal is logged under `### Removed` **and is a breaking entry** — bump minor in `0.x`, major in `1.0`. Never remove without a prior deprecation entry.\n\n\n## 8. Design philosophy","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#375","metadata":{"content":"ior deprecation entry.\n\n\n## 8. Design philosophy\n\n1. **Hybrid contract** — one file is both the data contract and its canonical documentation (the `design.md` lineage).\n2. **Core vs. profile** — the protocol is genre-agnostic; genres are profiles.\n3. **Data, not logic** — the contract says *what*; the engine implements *how*.\n4. **Single source of truth** — tokens edited once, never in generated output.\n5. **Graceful fallback** — the game never breaks if generated data is missing.\n6. **Determinism** — output is a pure function of source; CI rejects drift.\n7. **Zero dependencies** — custom parser, pure Node CLI.\n\n## 9. Conformance","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#376","metadata":{"content":"custom parser, pure Node CLI.\n\n## 9. Conformance\n\nGAME Protocol distinguishes the **reference implementation** (`tools/`) from the protocol itself. An alternative implementation is **conformant** if it satisfies all of the following:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#377","metadata":{"content":"nformant** if it satisfies all of the following:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#378","metadata":{"content":"formant** if it satisfies all of the following:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#379","metadata":{"content":"ormant** if it satisfies all of the following:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#38","metadata":{"content":"ble companion.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#380","metadata":{"content":"rmant** if it satisfies all of the following:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#381","metadata":{"content":"mant** if it satisfies all of the following:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#382","metadata":{"content":"ant** if it satisfies all of the following:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#383","metadata":{"content":"nt** if it satisfies all of the following:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#384","metadata":{"content":"t** if it satisfies all of the following:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#385","metadata":{"content":"** if it satisfies all of the following:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#386","metadata":{"content":"* if it satisfies all of the following:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#387","metadata":{"content":"if it satisfies all of the following:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#388","metadata":{"content":"if it satisfies all of the following:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#389","metadata":{"content":"f it satisfies all of the following:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#39","metadata":{"content":"le companion.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#390","metadata":{"content":"it satisfies all of the following:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#391","metadata":{"content":"it satisfies all of the following:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#392","metadata":{"content":"t satisfies all of the following:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#393","metadata":{"content":"satisfies all of the following:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#394","metadata":{"content":"satisfies all of the following:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#395","metadata":{"content":"atisfies all of the following:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#396","metadata":{"content":"tisfies all of the following:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#397","metadata":{"content":"isfies all of the following:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#398","metadata":{"content":"sfies all of the following:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#399","metadata":{"content":"fies all of the following:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#4","metadata":{"content":"n; `test/parser.js` is its executable companion.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#40","metadata":{"content":"e companion.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#400","metadata":{"content":"ies all of the following:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#401","metadata":{"content":"es all of the following:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#402","metadata":{"content":"s all of the following:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#403","metadata":{"content":"all of the following:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#404","metadata":{"content":"all of the following:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#405","metadata":{"content":"ll of the following:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#406","metadata":{"content":"l of the following:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#407","metadata":{"content":"of the following:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#408","metadata":{"content":"of the following:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#409","metadata":{"content":"f the following:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#41","metadata":{"content":"companion.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#410","metadata":{"content":"the following:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#411","metadata":{"content":"the following:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#412","metadata":{"content":"he following:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#413","metadata":{"content":"e following:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#414","metadata":{"content":"following:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#415","metadata":{"content":"following:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#416","metadata":{"content":"ollowing:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#417","metadata":{"content":"llowing:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#418","metadata":{"content":"lowing:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#419","metadata":{"content":"owing:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#42","metadata":{"content":"companion.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#420","metadata":{"content":"wing:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#421","metadata":{"content":"ing:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#422","metadata":{"content":"ng:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#423","metadata":{"content":"g:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#424","metadata":{"content":":","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#425","metadata":{"content":"1. **Parser.** It parses the YAML subset of §1.1 identically to the reference parser, including the hard-failure cases: block sequences (`- item`), front-matter lines without `:`, duplicate keys, unclosed strings, tab indentation, over-indentation, nesting deeper than 64 levels, and the forbidden keys `__proto__`/`constructor`/`prototype`. `test/parser.js` is the executable definition of these cases. Implementations MAY substitute a full YAML parser as long as the documented subset parses identically.\n2. **Linter.** It emits the core rules of §4 at the documented levels, executes the active profile's reference graph (`refs`, broken-ref family) and rule functions, and reports findings as `{level, rule, msg}` (plus `since`/`removedIn` at the `deprecated` level).","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#426","metadata":{"content":"s `since`/`removedIn` at the `deprecated` level). A document is valid iff it produces zero `error`-level findings. `test/conformance.js` is the executable reference: every valid example MUST lint clean and every invalid case MUST trigger its rule.\n3. **Compiler.** Its output is a pure function of the source (§3). For the reference artifact format (`window.GAME` as JSON), output MUST be byte-identical to `tools/game-export.js`: universal meta first (`generatedFrom`, `profile`, `name`, `description`, `platform`, `palettesCount`), then the profile's `derive` keys in declaration order, serialized as JSON with 2-space indent and LF line endings. The `profile` meta key lets multi-profile consumers dispatch a runtime without key-sniffing heuristics.\n4.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#427","metadata":{"content":"tch a runtime without key-sniffing heuristics.\n4. **Exit codes.** CLI surfaces follow the §3.1 contract (`0` OK / `1` validation, lint only / `2` input, profile or syntax). `test/cli-errors.js` is the executable reference.\n5. **Tolerance.** A conformant consumer MUST NOT reject a document because of: `x-` extension tokens or other unknown top-level tokens; findings at the `warn` or `deprecated` level (including an older `version`, §7); or Markdown body content beyond what `section-order` checks.\n6. **Round-trip.** A tool that rewrites a `GAME.md` (migrator, formatter, agent editor) MUST preserve tokens it does not understand — `x-` extensions and unknown keys included. Lossy rewriting breaks the experimentation contract of §7.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#428","metadata":{"content":"ting breaks the experimentation contract of §7.\n\nPoints 1–4 are the strict half of the contract (the gate); points 5–6 are the permissive half (what must *not* be enforced). Both halves are normative.\n\n## 10. Security & trust model\n\nTwo trust levels exist in the pipeline, and they must not be confused:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#429","metadata":{"content":"in the pipeline, and they must not be confused:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#43","metadata":{"content":"ompanion.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#430","metadata":{"content":"in the pipeline, and they must not be confused:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#431","metadata":{"content":"n the pipeline, and they must not be confused:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#432","metadata":{"content":"the pipeline, and they must not be confused:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#433","metadata":{"content":"the pipeline, and they must not be confused:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#434","metadata":{"content":"he pipeline, and they must not be confused:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#435","metadata":{"content":"e pipeline, and they must not be confused:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#436","metadata":{"content":"pipeline, and they must not be confused:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#437","metadata":{"content":"pipeline, and they must not be confused:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#438","metadata":{"content":"ipeline, and they must not be confused:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#439","metadata":{"content":"peline, and they must not be confused:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#44","metadata":{"content":"mpanion.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#440","metadata":{"content":"eline, and they must not be confused:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#441","metadata":{"content":"line, and they must not be confused:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#442","metadata":{"content":"ine, and they must not be confused:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#443","metadata":{"content":"ne, and they must not be confused:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#444","metadata":{"content":"e, and they must not be confused:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#445","metadata":{"content":", and they must not be confused:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#446","metadata":{"content":"and they must not be confused:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#447","metadata":{"content":"and they must not be confused:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#448","metadata":{"content":"nd they must not be confused:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#449","metadata":{"content":"d they must not be confused:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#45","metadata":{"content":"panion.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#450","metadata":{"content":"they must not be confused:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#451","metadata":{"content":"they must not be confused:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#452","metadata":{"content":"hey must not be confused:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#453","metadata":{"content":"ey must not be confused:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#454","metadata":{"content":"y must not be confused:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#455","metadata":{"content":"must not be confused:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#456","metadata":{"content":"must not be confused:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#457","metadata":{"content":"ust not be confused:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#458","metadata":{"content":"st not be confused:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#459","metadata":{"content":"t not be confused:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#46","metadata":{"content":"anion.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#460","metadata":{"content":"not be confused:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#461","metadata":{"content":"not be confused:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#462","metadata":{"content":"ot be confused:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#463","metadata":{"content":"t be confused:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#464","metadata":{"content":"be confused:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#465","metadata":{"content":"be confused:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#466","metadata":{"content":"e confused:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#467","metadata":{"content":"confused:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#468","metadata":{"content":"confused:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#469","metadata":{"content":"onfused:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#47","metadata":{"content":"nion.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#470","metadata":{"content":"nfused:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#471","metadata":{"content":"fused:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#472","metadata":{"content":"used:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#473","metadata":{"content":"sed:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#474","metadata":{"content":"ed:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#475","metadata":{"content":"d:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#476","metadata":{"content":":","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#477","metadata":{"content":"1. **`GAME.md` documents are untrusted input.** The tooling MUST be safe to run on a document from anywhere. The reference parser enforces this: forbidden keys (`__proto__`/`constructor`/`prototype`) block prototype pollution; the 64-level depth guard blocks stack-exhaustion input; every malformed construct fails fast with a parse error instead of degrading (§1.2). Neither lint nor export ever evaluates document content as code.\n2. **JS profiles are executable code and therefore trusted like a dependency.** `rules` functions and `derive.fn` run with full process privileges. The profile id regex (`/^[a-z0-9-]+$/`) prevents path traversal into arbitrary modules, and §6.1 validates the descriptor's *shape* — but neither can vet what a rule function *does*.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#478","metadata":{"content":"but neither can vet what a rule function *does*. **Review a third-party `.js` profile before installing it, exactly as you would review a dependency.**\n3. **Pure-data profiles (`.json`, §6.1) are safe to load from third parties.** They are parsed, never executed: the worst a malicious `quiz.json` can do is emit wrong findings or derive wrong keys. This is the supported path for community profiles; `.js` profiles remain in-repo under CODEOWNERS review.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#479","metadata":{"content":"profiles remain in-repo under CODEOWNERS review.\n\nAdditional hardening in the reference tools: `render-png.js` loads generated artifacts via `require()` confined to `examples/` (no `eval`/`new Function`, path-checked against traversal); `GAME_ENGINE` cross-checks read engine source as **text** (tokenized, never executed); generated artifacts are written only after a successful compile, never partially.\n\n## 11. Future directions (non-normative)\n\nDocumented so the trade-offs are explicit; none of this is part of `0.1`:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#48","metadata":{"content":"ion.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#480","metadata":{"content":"ffs are explicit; none of this is part of `0.1`:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#481","metadata":{"content":"fs are explicit; none of this is part of `0.1`:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#482","metadata":{"content":"s are explicit; none of this is part of `0.1`:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#483","metadata":{"content":"are explicit; none of this is part of `0.1`:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#484","metadata":{"content":"are explicit; none of this is part of `0.1`:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#485","metadata":{"content":"re explicit; none of this is part of `0.1`:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#486","metadata":{"content":"e explicit; none of this is part of `0.1`:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#487","metadata":{"content":"explicit; none of this is part of `0.1`:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#488","metadata":{"content":"explicit; none of this is part of `0.1`:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#489","metadata":{"content":"xplicit; none of this is part of `0.1`:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#49","metadata":{"content":"on.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#490","metadata":{"content":"plicit; none of this is part of `0.1`:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#491","metadata":{"content":"licit; none of this is part of `0.1`:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#492","metadata":{"content":"icit; none of this is part of `0.1`:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#493","metadata":{"content":"cit; none of this is part of `0.1`:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#494","metadata":{"content":"it; none of this is part of `0.1`:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#495","metadata":{"content":"t; none of this is part of `0.1`:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#496","metadata":{"content":"; none of this is part of `0.1`:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#497","metadata":{"content":"none of this is part of `0.1`:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#498","metadata":{"content":"none of this is part of `0.1`:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#499","metadata":{"content":"one of this is part of `0.1`:","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_type":"Documentation","title":"GAME Protocol — Core Specification"}},{"id":"SPEC.md#5","metadata":{"content":"; `test/parser.js` is its executable companion.","okf_concept":"SPEC.md","okf_